Preheat your #oven{} to 180℃. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%can} in a #colander{}. Pop a third of the beans in a #bowl{} and mash with a #fork{} until broken up. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lime{½}. Chop the @halloumi{250%g} into 2cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. Add the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g}, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @water{100%ml} and add the whole and crushed beans. Mix together and cook for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add half the @chipotle paste{20%g} to the beans. Mix well and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Allow to simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the halloumi and fry until golden, ~{6-7%minutes}. Turn every ~{2%minutes}. Meanwhile, mix the remaining chipotle paste and half the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} in a small bowl.

Pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} (3 per person) directly onto the top shelf of the oven until heated through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Mix the remaining mayo with the lime zest. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then half lengthways. Thinly slice widthways.

Lay the tacos on a #board{} or #plate{}. Spread the chipotle mayo on the base of the tacos. Add a handful of lettuce to the base and squeeze over the lime juice. Add a couple of spoonfuls of the chipotle bean mix to each taco. Top with equal amounts of halloumi cubes, drizzle over the limey mayo. Serve 3 per person with any extra lime wedges for squeezing over. Dig in!

